<h2>The Iterative Signature Algorithm</h2>

<h3>The <strong>isa2</strong> R package</h3>

<p>
Use this package if you want to apply the ISA to a data set other than
gene expression data. It is part of
the <a href="http://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/isa2/index.html">standard
    R package repository</a>, so you can install it directly from
there.
<p class="more">
<a href="isa2.html">Read more &raquo;</a>
</p>

<h3>The <strong>eisa</strong> R package</h3>

<p>
The <strong>eisa</strong> package builds on <strong>isa2</strong> and
provides a convenient interface to analyze gene expression data. It
uses standard <a href="http://www.bioconductor.org">BioConductor</a>
packages and classes.
</p>
<p class="more" >
<a href="eisa.html">Read more &raquo;</a>
</p>

<h3>ISA in Matlab</h3>

<p>
If you prefer using Matlab instead of R, we also created a Matlab
implementation of the ISA.
</p>
<p class="more">
<a href="isamatlab.html">Read more &raquo;</a>
</p>

